    <stitle>Bosch Parking Brake: Manual or Power Brake - PARK BRAKE CABLE ADJUSTMENT: MANUAL BRAKE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="3">
        <title>PARK BRAKE CABLE ADJUSTMENT: MANUAL BRAKE</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Do not let the handle snap back when the tool is off the cable. The tool will be damaged.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f0404404" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404404.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="408px"
                     scalefitheight="432px"/>
            <caption>Figure 1. Parking Brake System Overview: Manual Brake</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BRAKE CABLE ADJUSTMENT TURNBUCKLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. PARKING BRAKE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0404405" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404406.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 2. Tension Measuring Tool</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. INDICATING BAR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set parking brake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the park brake cable adjustment turnbuckle in the left frame rail
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404404">(Figure 1).</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Check cable tension immediately forward of the turnbuckle
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0404404">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Depress the tool handle fully so that the wheel will engage the far side of the cable
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404406">(Figure 3)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0404406" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404405.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 3. Tension Measuring Tool Handles Depressed</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WHEEL</callout1>
                <callout1>2. INDICATING BAR</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Correct cable tension for adjustment of a new (replacement) cable is 500 &#177; 25 lb.</para>
            </note>
            <note>
                <para>Correct cable tension for adjustment of existing cable is 390 &#177; 25 lb.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the handle quickly but smoothly and read the direct tension units on the dial face
                next to the indicating bar
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404406">(Figure 3)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <para>If tension is incorrect, remove tool, release park brake, and re-adjust tension using the park brake cable
            turnbuckle
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404404">(Figure 1)</hotlnk>. Recheck cable tension. Repeat steps 1-4 until tension is
            within correct limits.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set and release the park brake five times then check tension. If tension is within correct
                limits the operation is complete. If the tension is not within correct limits repeat steps 1-5.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
